byline.original: By LESLIE PICKER and MICHAEL J. de la MERCED

abstract: Initial public offering market has fallen significantly after several winning years; 144 firms have priced IPOs to date in 2015, down 36 percent from year-ago; volatility in private equity markets is seen as factor.
lead_paragraph: First Data, the payments company, priced its offering below the expected range, and the supermarket chain Albertsons elected to delay its offering.

headline.main: Companies Eyeing Public Offerings Reckon With Inhospitable Market
